  "elapsed_s": 398.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in the general context, global context, they were not-- apparently not well prepared.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't have even-- their-- their clothes and their military uniforms were also second- or third-rated.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when the war started in June 21, the Russians panicked and they start looking for refuge.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they start rushing with any type of vehicle that was available.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And some Jews were able also to mount them and to go deep back to Russia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My position was to run also to-- to my city, but I found myself, after reaching the highway, that we were strifed by German planes.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And many of those people, civilians, who tried to run away and to go towards north, were killed and-- by the oncoming German-- German planes.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I decided to go back to Kaunas and to be with my uncle, my grandmother, and my aunt.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my little cousin was just born.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I mention the cousin, because later on, I would have to explain to you about Harry.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we found ourselves now, the radio blasted saying that Lithuanians, as you know, they were favoring-- they hated the Russians.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were favoring the Germans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And right away, this elite of the Lithuanians start blasting through the radio, saying that they have noticed that the German-- victorious German troops are approaching Lithuania and the capital.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they have heard that some Jewish-- the communists and Jews are trying to intervene and to obstruct the victorious entry of their German army.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And for each-- for each German or Lithuanian that will be killed by the communist and Jews, 100 Jews are going to be, at random, put to the wall and shot.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
